{"title_page": "New Mother", "text_new": "{{short description|1999 album}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2018}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = New Mother\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[Angels of Light]]\n| cover      = Angels_of_Light_New_Mother.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = April 5, 1999<ref name=\"releasedate\">{{cite web| url=http://swans.pair.com/news.html| title=SWANS NEWS| accessdate=August 9, 2017| url-status=bot: unknown| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/19990423084637/http://swans.pair.com/news.html| archivedate=April 23, 1999| df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     = Ethel Sound/Triclops <small>([[Atlanta, Georgia]])</small> <br/> King Mattress <small>([[Atlanta, Georgia]])</small> <br/> B.C. Studios <small>([[Brooklyn, New York]])</small> <br/> Spa Recording <small>([[New York City, New York]])</small>\n| genre      = [[Experimental rock]], [[folk rock]], [[post-rock]], [[baroque pop]]\n| length     = 71:22\n| label      = [[Young God Records|Young God]]\n| producer   = [[Michael Gira]]\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title = [[How I Loved You]]\n| next_year  = 2001\n}}\n{{Album ratings\n| rev1      = [[Allmusic]]\n| rev1Score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"allmusic\">{{cite web | url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/new-mother-mw0000256935 | title=Angels of Light - New Mother | publisher=[[Allmusic]] | accessdate=March 8, 2014 | author=Raggett, Ned}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''New Mother''''' is the debut studio album by American [[folk music]] act [[Angels of Light]]. It was released on April 5, 1999 via frontman Michael Gira's own record label [[Young God Records]], immediately after Michael Gira disbanded his previous band, [[Swans (band)|Swans]]. The album features contributions from various musicians, including violinist [[Hahn Rowe]], [[Rasputina (band)|Rasputina band]] cellist [[Julia Kent]], drummer [[Thor Harris]], composer [[Joe McGinty]] and ex-Swans members [[Bill Rieflin]], [[Phil Puleo]] and Bill Bronson.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://younggodrecords.com/new-mother | title=\"New Mother\" on Young God Records | accessdate=March 8, 2014 | author=Gira, Michael}}</ref>\n\nThe album contains versions of some songs that were performed live during [[Swans (band)|Swans]] final tour, including \"The Man With the Silver Tongue\" and \"Not Alone\". The [[Michael Gira]] solo album ''Solo Recording at Home'' contains an outtake from the recordings session for this album, on the song \"God's Servant\".\n\n==Critical reception==\nNed Raggett of [[Allmusic]] gave the album a positive review, stating: \"No less than 19 musicians participated in the creation of ''New Mother'', and the fact that Gira was able to synthesize their efforts and create such a powerful debut bodes well for his future efforts in this vein.\" He also wrote that the record \"draws on a juxtaposition of lush '60s American and European pop orchestration.\"<ref name=\"allmusic\" /> Jordan N. Mamone of [[CMJ]] also praised the album, writing: \"While many of the Swans' attempts at levity sounded forced and [[Gothic rock|gothic]], the Angels of Light shine naturally, with poise and stunning clarity.\"<ref name=\"cmj-review\">{{cite journal | url=https://books.google.com/?id=ypZypqzY1lAC&pg=PA3&dq=%22New+Mother%22+angels+of+light#v=onepage&q=%22New%20Mother%22%20angels%20of%20light&f=false | title=Angels of Light _ New Mother | author=Mamone, Jordan N. | journal=[[CMJ]] |date=May 1999  | volume=58 | issue=617 | pages=3 | issn=0890-0795}}</ref> He subsequently included the album in his \"Top Ten Picks\" list.<ref>{{cite journal | url=https://books.google.com/?id=4wjPUdBdZZcC&pg=PA33&dq=%22New+Mother%22+angels+of+light#v=onepage&q=%22New%20Mother%22%20angels%20of%20light&f=false | title=Staff Top Ten Picks | author=Mamone, Jordan N. | journal=[[CMJ]] |date=January 2000  | volume=61 | issue=649 | pages=33 | issn=0890-0795 }}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n\n{{tracklist\n| headline = Side One\n| title1 = Fragment\n| length1 = 0:31\n| title2 = Praise Your Name\n| length2 = 4:48\n| title3 = New Mother\n| length3 = 4:35\n| title4 = Angels of Light\n| length4 = 6:53\n| total_length = 16:47\n}}\n{{tracklist\n| headline = Side Two\n| title5 = Inner Female\n| length5 = 4:47\n| title6 = This Is Mine\n| length6 = 4:17\n| title7 = Shame\n| length7 = 4:10\n| title8 = Intermission\n| length8 = 1:14\n| title9 = The Man With the Silver Tongue\n| length9 = 4:13\n| total_length = 18:41\n}}\n{{tracklist\n| headline = Side Three\n| title10 = Real Person\n| length10 = 5:09\n| title11 = Forever Yours\n| length11 = 5:16\n| title12 = How We End\n| length12 = 3:25\n| title13 = The Garden Hides the Jewel\n| length13 = 5:21\n| total_length = 19:11\n}}\n{{tracklist\n| headline = Side Four\n| title14 = Not Alone\n| length14 = 4:33\n| title15 = Song for My Father\n| length15 = 3:41\n| title16 = His Entropic Highness\n| length16 = 5:33\n| title17 = Fear of Death\n| length17 = 2:56\n| total_length= 16:43 (71:22)\n}}\n\n==Personnel==\n;Angels of Light\n*[[Michael Gira]]&nbsp;\u2013 vocals, composition, production, acoustic guitar, electric guitar\n\n;Additional musicians\n*[[Bill Rieflin]]&nbsp;\u2013 piano, bass guitar, [[Farfisa|Farfisa organ]], [[Hammond organ|B3 organ]], analog synthesizer, acoustic guitar, backingvocals\n*Christoph Hahn&nbsp;\u2013 lap steel, classical and electric guitar, Cassio organ, backing vocals\n*Larry Mullins&nbsp;\u2013 vibraphone, timpani, tabla, percussion, backing vocals\n*[[Thor Harris]]&nbsp;\u2013 hand drums, percussion, glockenspiel, backing vocals, water bowls\n*[[Phil Puleo]]&nbsp;\u2013 percussion, melodica, organ, mouth harp\n*[[Julia Kent]]&nbsp;\u2013 cello\n*Bill Bronson&nbsp;\u2013 bass guitar \n*[[Joe McGinty]]&nbsp;\u2013 upright piano\n*[[Michele Amar]]&nbsp;\u2013 backing vocals\n*[[Hahn Rowe]]&nbsp;\u2013 violin\n*Birgit Staudt&nbsp;\u2013 accordion\n*Thomas Dodd&nbsp;\u2013 [[Celtic harp|Irish harp]] \n*[[Martin Bisi]]&nbsp;\u2013 organ, backing vocals, engineering, mixing\n*Chris Griffin&nbsp;\u2013 banjo, dobro, dulcimer, mandolin\n \n;Other personnel\n*Hillary Johnson&nbsp;\u2013 assistant engineering, engineering\n*Michael Moore&nbsp;\u2013 engineering\n\n==Chart positions==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! width=\"200\"| Chart (1999)\n!Peak<br />position\n|-\n| ''[[CMJ]]'' Radio 200<ref>{{cite journal | url=https://books.google.com/?id=aCLLK8t9Ob8C&pg=PA17&dq=%22New+Mother%22+angels+of+light#v=onepage&q=%22New%20Mother%22%20angels%20of%20light&f=false | title=CMJ Radio 200 | journal=[[CMJ]] |date=September 1999  | volume=59 | issue=634 | pages=17 |issn= 0890-0795| author1=Cmj Network | first1=Inc }}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|74\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://younggodrecords.com/new-mother New Mother on Young God Records]\n\n{{Michael Gira}}\n\n[[Category:1999 debut albums]]\n[[Category:Angels of Light albums]]\n[[Category:Young God Records albums]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Michael Gira]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|1999 album}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2018}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = New Mother\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[Angels of Light]]\n| cover      = Angels_of_Light_New_Mother.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = April 5, 1999<ref name=\"releasedate\">{{cite web| url=http://swans.pair.com/news.html| title=SWANS NEWS| accessdate=August 9, 2017| url-status=bot: unknown| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/19990423084637/http://swans.pair.com/news.html| archivedate=April 23, 1999| df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     = Ethel Sound/Triclops <small>([[Atlanta, Georgia]])</small> <br/> King Mattress <small>([[Atlanta, Georgia]])</small> <br/> B.C. Studios <small>([[Brooklyn, New York]])</small> <br/> Spa Recording <small>([[New York City, New York]])</small>\n| genre      = [[Experimental rock]], [[folk rock]], [[post-rock]], [[baroque pop]]\n| length     = 71:22\n| label      = [[Young God Records|Young God]]\n| producer   = [[Michael Gira]]\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title = [[How I Loved You]]\n| next_year  = 2001\n}}\n{{Album ratings\n| rev1      = [[Allmusic]]\n| rev1Score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"allmusic\">{{cite web | url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/new-mother-mw0000256935 | title=Angels of Light - New Mother | publisher=[[Allmusic]] | accessdate=March 8, 2014 | author=Raggett, Ned}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''New Mother''''' is the debut studio album by American [[folk music]] act, [[Angels of Light]]. It was released on April 5, 1999 via frontman Michael Gira's own record label [[Young God Records]], immediately after Michael Gira disbanded his previous band, [[Swans (band)|Swans]]. The album features contributions from various musicians, including violinist [[Hahn Rowe]], [[Rasputina (band)|Rasputina band]] cellist [[Julia Kent]], drummer [[Thor Harris]], composer [[Joe McGinty]] and ex-Swans members [[Bill Rieflin]], [[Phil Puleo]] and Bill Bronson.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://younggodrecords.com/new-mother | title=\"New Mother\" on Young God Records | accessdate=March 8, 2014 | author=Gira, Michael}}</ref>\n\nThe album contains versions of some songs that were performed live during [[Swans (band)|Swans]] final tour, including \"The Man With the Silver Tongue\" and \"Not Alone\". The [[Michael Gira]] solo album ''Solo Recording at Home'' contains an outtake from the recordings session for this album, on the song \"God's Servant\".\n\n==Critical reception==\nNed Raggett of [[Allmusic]] gave the album a positive review, stating: \"No less than 19 musicians participated in the creation of ''New Mother'', and the fact that Gira was able to synthesize their efforts and create such a powerful debut bodes well for his future efforts in this vein.\" He also wrote that the record \"draws on a juxtaposition of lush '60s American and European pop orchestration.\"<ref name=\"allmusic\" /> Jordan N. Mamone of [[CMJ]] also praised the album, writing: \"While many of the Swans' attempts at levity sounded forced and [[Gothic rock|gothic]], the Angels of Light shine naturally, with poise and stunning clarity.\"<ref name=\"cmj-review\">{{cite journal | url=https://books.google.com/?id=ypZypqzY1lAC&pg=PA3&dq=%22New+Mother%22+angels+of+light#v=onepage&q=%22New%20Mother%22%20angels%20of%20light&f=false | title=Angels of Light _ New Mother | author=Mamone, Jordan N. | journal=[[CMJ]] |date=May 1999  | volume=58 | issue=617 | pages=3 | issn=0890-0795}}</ref> He subsequently included the album in his \"Top Ten Picks\" list.<ref>{{cite journal | url=https://books.google.com/?id=4wjPUdBdZZcC&pg=PA33&dq=%22New+Mother%22+angels+of+light#v=onepage&q=%22New%20Mother%22%20angels%20of%20light&f=false | title=Staff Top Ten Picks | author=Mamone, Jordan N. | journal=[[CMJ]] |date=January 2000  | volume=61 | issue=649 | pages=33 | issn=0890-0795 }}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n\n{{tracklist\n| headline = Side One\n| title1 = Fragment\n| length1 = 0:31\n| title2 = Praise Your Name\n| length2 = 4:48\n| title3 = New Mother\n| length3 = 4:35\n| title4 = Angels of Light\n| length4 = 6:53\n| total_length = 16:47\n}}\n{{tracklist\n| headline = Side Two\n| title5 = Inner Female\n| length5 = 4:47\n| title6 = This Is Mine\n| length6 = 4:17\n| title7 = Shame\n| length7 = 4:10\n| title8 = Intermission\n| length8 = 1:14\n| title9 = The Man With the Silver Tongue\n| length9 = 4:13\n| total_length = 18:41\n}}\n{{tracklist\n| headline = Side Three\n| title10 = Real Person\n| length10 = 5:09\n| title11 = Forever Yours\n| length11 = 5:16\n| title12 = How We End\n| length12 = 3:25\n| title13 = The Garden Hides the Jewel\n| length13 = 5:21\n| total_length = 19:11\n}}\n{{tracklist\n| headline = Side Four\n| title14 = Not Alone\n| length14 = 4:33\n| title15 = Song for My Father\n| length15 = 3:41\n| title16 = His Entropic Highness\n| length16 = 5:33\n| title17 = Fear of Death\n| length17 = 2:56\n| total_length= 16:43 (71:22)\n}}\n\n==Personnel==\n;Angels of Light\n*[[Michael Gira]]&nbsp;\u2013 vocals, composition, production, acoustic guitar, electric guitar\n\n;Additional musicians\n*[[Bill Rieflin]]&nbsp;\u2013 piano, bass guitar, [[Farfisa|Farfisa organ]], [[Hammond organ|B3 organ]], analog synthesizer, acoustic guitar, backingvocals\n*Christoph Hahn&nbsp;\u2013 lap steel, classical and electric guitar, Cassio organ, backing vocals\n*Larry Mullins&nbsp;\u2013 vibraphone, timpani, tabla, percussion, backing vocals\n*[[Thor Harris]]&nbsp;\u2013 hand drums, percussion, glockenspiel, backing vocals, water bowls\n*[[Phil Puleo]]&nbsp;\u2013 percussion, melodica, organ, mouth harp\n*[[Julia Kent]]&nbsp;\u2013 cello\n*Bill Bronson&nbsp;\u2013 bass guitar \n*[[Joe McGinty]]&nbsp;\u2013 upright piano\n*[[Michele Amar]]&nbsp;\u2013 backing vocals\n*[[Hahn Rowe]]&nbsp;\u2013 violin\n*Birgit Staudt&nbsp;\u2013 accordion\n*Thomas Dodd&nbsp;\u2013 [[Celtic harp|Irish harp]] \n*[[Martin Bisi]]&nbsp;\u2013 organ, backing vocals, engineering, mixing\n*Chris Griffin&nbsp;\u2013 banjo, dobro, dulcimer, mandolin\n \n;Other personnel\n*Hillary Johnson&nbsp;\u2013 assistant engineering, engineering\n*Michael Moore&nbsp;\u2013 engineering\n\n==Chart positions==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! width=\"200\"| Chart (1999)\n!Peak<br />position\n|-\n| ''[[CMJ]]'' Radio 200<ref>{{cite journal | url=https://books.google.com/?id=aCLLK8t9Ob8C&pg=PA17&dq=%22New+Mother%22+angels+of+light#v=onepage&q=%22New%20Mother%22%20angels%20of%20light&f=false | title=CMJ Radio 200 | journal=[[CMJ]] |date=September 1999  | volume=59 | issue=634 | pages=17 |issn= 0890-0795| author1=Cmj Network | first1=Inc }}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|74\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://younggodrecords.com/new-mother New Mother on Young God Records]\n\n{{Michael Gira}}\n\n[[Category:1999 debut albums]]\n[[Category:Angels of Light albums]]\n[[Category:Young God Records albums]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Michael Gira]]\n", "name_user": "Shingpau", "