 touch before three goals from Brownfield secured the title for Mavericks. <ref name=\"womensport080408\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.womensportreport.com/what-a-match-mavericks-def/wn/208|title=What a match! Mavericks def Loughborough Lightning in Super League Final|publisher=www.womensportreport.com|accessdate=3 April 2020|date=6 April 2008}}</ref><ref name=\"express050408\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.express.co.uk/netball/40383/Superleague-victory-for-Mavericks|title=Superleague victory for Mavericks|publisher=www.express.co.uk|accessdate=5 April 2020|date=5 April 2008}}</ref><ref name=\"whtimes060408\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.whtimes.co.uk/sport/third-time-lucky-for-magnificent-mavericks-1-15894|title=Third time lucky for magnificent Mavericks|publisher=www.whtimes.co.uk|accessdate=3 February 2020|date=6 April 2008}}</ref><ref name=\"lewes050408\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.lewesnetballclub.co.uk/pg_super_league.html|title=Super leauge &#91;sic&#93; final 5th April 2008|publisher=www.lewesnetballclub.co.uk|accessdate=3 April 2020|date=5 April 2008}}</ref><ref name=\"sportsister080408\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.sportsister.com/2008/04/08/mavericks-win-netball-superleague-final/|title=Mavericks win Netball Superleague final|publisher=www.sportsister.com|accessdate=4 February 2020|date=8 April 2008}}</ref>\n\n==Route to the Final==\n{{see|2007\u201308 Netball Superleague season}}\n\n==Match summary==\n{{netballbox\n | bg         = #EEEEEE\n | date       = 5 April 2008\n | time       = \n | report     = \n | stats      = \n | team1      = [[Galleria Mavericks]]\n | score1     = 43\n | team2      = [[Loughborough Lightning (netball)|Loughborough Lightning]]\n | score2     = 39\n | Q1         = 6\u20139\n | Q2         = 14\u201321\n | Q3         = 28\u201331\n | Q4         = 43\u201339\n | H1         = \n | H2         = \n | ET         = \n | goals1     = [[Louisa Brownfield]] {{nb-goal|33|38}} ?<br>Michelle Hall {{nb-goal|9|11}}<br>Monique Wood {{nb-goal|2|7}}\n | o